Great Dynamic Cooperative Society is to roll out a N20 million economic empowerment loan scheme for its members. The general manager of the cooperative, Mr. Taiwo Owolanu, stated this in Abuja while addressing journalists as part of activities lined up to mark the one year anniversary of the group. Specifically, the financial group stated that the loan scheme was designed to assist members in commercial farming, trade and commerce in line with the diversification policy of the present government. The GM stressed the need for financial institutions in the country to assist government achieve its diversification policy by investing in small and medium scale enterprises, just as he identified the micro enterprise as the economic base of any developing society.